steps.prompt:
You are an expert developer creating component documentation. Based on the component specification and information, create comprehensive usage documentation following the template structure.

Component Specification:
{{generated_spec}}

Component ID: {{component_id}}
Component Name: {{component_name}}
Module Path: {{module_path|default:''}}
Component Type: {{component_type|default:''}}
Language: {{language|default:'python'}}

Documentation Template:
{{doc_template}}

Use the following guides for context:
<SPEC_DOC_GUIDE>
{{spec_doc_guide}}
</SPEC_DOC_GUIDE>

<IMPLEMENTATION_PHILOSOPHY>
{{implementation_philosophy}}
</IMPLEMENTATION_PHILOSOPHY>

IMPORTANT GUIDELINES:
1. Create complete, detailed documentation for the component in {{language|default:'python'}} language
2. Include clear examples using {{language|default:'python'}} syntax
3. For TypeScript/JavaScript components, use appropriate idioms (imports, interfaces, types, etc.)
4. For React components, include component props and usage examples with JSX
5. Within the documentation, use the component_id ("{{component_id}}") as the base name for all classes, modules, and file references unless explicitly overridden in the candidate spec
6. Format your response as a FileGenerationResult with a single file named "{{component_id}}.md"

Do not include the component name or other text in the filename - it must be exactly "{{component_id}}.md".
